\ddot\theta = \frac{\mathrm d\dot\theta}{\mathrm dt} = \frac{\mathrm d}{\mathrm dt}\left(\frac{v\sin(\theta)}{r}\right) = \frac{\dot v \sin (\theta) }{r} + \frac{v\dot \theta \cos(\theta)}{r} - \frac{v\sin(\theta)}{r^2}\dot r
